{
  "texts": [
    "-𝔼𝔼 q(c,|,x)q(u) [D KL (q(z|c, x)‖p(z|u, c;σ))]",
    "-D KL (q(c|x;α)||p(c;α, A))",
    "where D KL (p || q) is the Kullback-Leibler divergence between distribution p and q, defined as D KL (p || q) = 𝔼 p(x) [log p(x)/q(x)].",
    "We find the q that maximizes the ELBO by running stochastic gradient descent.",
    "To integrate the histology in the inference method, we model the approximate posterior over the latent low-dimensional representation z with the PoE distributions (Supplementary Fig. 1a)."
  ]
